snippet.textDisplay: What an amazing win by England.  The creativity and strength shown by both teams was incredible.  But I have to say my favourite shots are the ones that are just guided to the boundary for 4 by the batsmen.  Bairstow is incredible to watch when he's on song - some of the cricket shots he plays are sublime.  Shot of the day for me though is a 4 hit by Stokes at about 12 mins in - he just left his bat for the ball to hit it and it sped away for 4.  I say 'just' as if anyone could do it, but such incredible skill.  Some fantastic crowd catches too, I can't remember ever seeing as many crowd catches...

snippet.textDisplay:
Hard hitting but lets face it, the bowling from both sides was crap. I can hardly get my arm over at all but I am sure the batsman would have more difficulty scoring so many sixes if I had been bowling, or any of the bowlers at my club side, simply because of our complete lack of pace and better line. All these batsmens need is plenty of muscle, good eye hand coordination, and a bit of luck. With only 20 overs, and a very long batting line up even luck is no longer so much of an issue.
Having said that, it has been a great tour all round, with plenty of finely balanced and exciting games. The only real negative is that the South African audience only seem to turn up at one dayers, which is simply not good enough. If you don't use it, you lose it. If the South African public don't make a show when such great test matches are on view, then when will they?
